---
/**
 * domain-agent-design 0001 · Figure 3 — "Runtime = the agent loop + limits + gates".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/domain-agent-design/lessons/0001-the-domain-agent-design-method.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup id="r5">). Lives as an
 * .astro component for the same reason as Fig1. References #arw, #arwR and #arwM,
 * embedded as a local <defs> so the url(#…) refs resolve inside this svg.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The agent runtime: an observe-think-act loop where tool calls pass through limits and approval gates, with retrieved context and memory feeding the window."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwM"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#3d54c9"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Runtime = the agent loop + limits + gates</text
        >

        <!-- the loop -->
        <rect
            x="60"
            y="44"
            width="120"
            height="40"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eceef9"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="120" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >observe</text
        >
        <text x="120" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >request + tool results</text
        >
        <rect
            x="260"
            y="44"
            width="120"
            height="40"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eceef9"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >think (LLM)</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >choose next action</text
        >
        <rect
            x="460"
            y="44"
            width="120"
            height="40"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eceef9"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="520" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >act (tool)</text
        >
        <text x="520" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >call the surface</text
        >

        <line x1="180" y1="64" x2="256" y2="64" stroke="#3d54c9" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
        <line x1="380" y1="64" x2="456" y2="64" stroke="#3d54c9" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
        <!-- loop back -->
        <path
            d="M520,84 C520,120 120,120 120,86"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-dasharray="4 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwM)"></path>
        <text x="320" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >repeat until done or limit hit</text
        >

        <!-- feeds into context -->
        <rect x="60" y="150" width="220" height="38" rx="8" fill="#f4f4f6" stroke="#6b675f"></rect>
        <text x="170" y="166" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >3 Context + 4 Memory</text
        >
        <text x="170" y="180" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >curated window, retrieved state</text
        >
        <line
            x1="170"
            y1="150"
            x2="170"
            y2="124"
            stroke="#6b675f"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <text x="200" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#6b675f">into observe</text>

        <!-- limits + gates band -->
        <rect x="300" y="150" width="280" height="38" rx="8" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="440" y="166" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >limits (5) + gates (8) sit on "act"</text
        >
        <text x="440" y="180" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >step cap &middot; cost cap &middot; high-blast tools pause for a human</text
        >
        <line
            x1="500"
            y1="150"
            x2="510"
            y2="86"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>

        <rect x="60" y="206" width="520" height="32" rx="7" fill="#eceef9" stroke="#3d54c9"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="226" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >The reason-then-act loop is what makes it an agent, not a chatbot &mdash; grounding
            each action in the last observation.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The runtime wraps the <b>observe &rarr; think &rarr; act</b> loop with the things that keep it
        safe: a step/cost limit so it can't run forever, and approval gates on the <em>act</em> step for
        high-blast tools. Reasoning interleaved with acting &mdash; grounding actions in observations
        &mdash; is the pattern underneath every domain agent.<sup><a href="#s4" id="r5">4</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
